A survey done by global audit firm KPMG shows that 76% of the workers from east Africa agree that the HR function has undergone a digital transformation through the use of online recruitment, candidate shortlisting and integration of employee measures of productivity. This simply put means that more job seekers are active on online recruitment platforms as opposed to the old CV's. According to the survey, HR executives in east Africa ranked high in performance management, learning and re?skilling and staff retention as the main areas that most organizations practice.